In p-type PbTe, the small offset between light valence band (L) and heavy valence band (Σ) facilitates charge redistribution from single band to multiple bands. Elements alloying could enclose the light and heavy valence bands, called band convergence. Converging valence bands could enhance effective mass through increasing valley degeneracy numbers.3,71 Recently, the approach of band convergence was revisited along with nanostructuring technology, which is one powerful synergistic strategy to enhance thermoelectric performance in p-type PbTe.62,72 Band convergence can achieve a high valley degeneracy number (Nv) to enlarge the effective mass (m*), defined as m*=Nv2∕3mb*\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
